Without knowing any of the details, I guess the added vector exposed some error about alignment, because it changes the size and thus `alignof(PickFirst)`. Causing the memory to be alloc'ed with `gpr_malloc_aligned` but freed with `gpr_free` rather than `gpr_free_aligned`.

My guess is when you `New` the object, it is a `PickFirst` which requires aligned alloc, while you delete it, it is from base class so the `Delete` sees a type of `LBPolicy` which does not require aligned alloc.

Nice psychic debugging!! Indeed, changing `kAlignmentForDefaultAllocationInBytes ` to 16 fixes this crash ([here](https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/master/src/core/lib/gprpp/memory.h#L44)).

Is there a _right_ way to fix this at the moment? Or is this something being addressed by @nicolasnoble's  changes
